#Try the Direct RPM Installation Method
Skip the repository setup and download VS Code directly:

# Download the latest RPM package
wget -O vscode.rpm "https://code.visualstudio.com/sha/download?build=stable&os=linux-rpm-x64"

# Install using yum (it will handle dependencies)
sudo yum install ./vscode.rpm

Now go to vscode and install python extension

open terminal and create a folder
then in terminal change directory to the folder you created

pip env install django #this will install django virtual environment
